Inspecting devices in Linux: 
sudo lspi: shows all devices that are connected to the PCI BURST
sudo lspci -s 00:03.0 -v
sudo lspci -s 00:03.0 -k 

identify devices connectect by usv
sudo lsusb 
sudo lsub -that

**Kernel Modules**
sudo lsmod: list the kernel Modules
sudo lsmod |fgrep -i snd


sudo modprobe -r <module-name>: unload the module 
sudo modinfo module-name: get information about module
sudo modinfo -p module-name: 


